The polynomial \(p(x)\) is given to have degree 1008, so \(N = 1008\) and \(d = N - 1008 = 0\). For the second part, we need the smallest \(r > 0\) such that there exist differentiable functions \(f\) and \(g\) satisfying the conditions. From the inequalities \(|f'| \leq |g|\) and \(|g'| \leq |f|\) with \(f(0) > 0\) and \(g(0) = 0\), we derive that \(|f(x)| \geq f(0) \cos x\), so if \(f(r) = 0\), then \(\cos r \leq 0\), implying \(r \geq \pi/2\). The functions \(f(x) = f(0) \cos x\) and \(g(x) = f(0) \sin x\) show that \(r = \pi/2\) works, and no smaller \(r\) is possible.

